    "analysis": "Trace-level scan completed: we computed global P95/P5 per (cmdb_id, trace_name) and applied them to the 08:30–09:00 window. The result shows every scanned trace series flagged as anomalous (anomaly_count_in_window = 30 for many series). This is likely a thresholding artifact because many trace series are zero-dominated (global P95 and P5 = 0.0), so the current anomaly rule (value >= P95 OR value <= P5) marks zero/tiny values as anomalies. Thus trace results are not reliably separating real failures. Meanwhile, error_logs.csv is concentrated on frontend-0/1/2 with warning messages referencing 'failed to retrieve...' and timestamps that overlap the incident window. Metric-level aggregation flagged many components (notably frontend*, adservice*, checkoutservice*, productcatalogservice*) with earliest anomalies at the window start (1647736200). To localize two distinct failures, we should now analyze logs (error_logs.csv and normalized log.csv) to find concrete failure times (peaks of error messages and nonzero log.error_count) and identify which pod(s) first showed errors. This will provide precise occurrence timestamps and candidate root components to then confirm with targeted metric traces.",
