    "instruction": "From the kernel state use frontend_series_table (the selected frontend KPI snapshot table) and do the following bounded retrievals:\n1) Take up to the first 30 rows of frontend_series_table (sorted as it currently is). For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) in those rows, extract metric.csv rows where cmdb_id and kpi_name match and timestamp is in the set of candidate minutes ± 120 seconds: {1647736200,1647736380,1647736680,1647736920,1647737040,1647737280} extended by ±120s (i.e., include timestamps between minute-120 and minute+120 for each candidate minute). Return for each series a compact listing: cmdb_id, kpi_name, then the matching (timestamp,value) pairs sorted by timestamp. Limit total returned rows across all series so output remains compact.\n2) Extract full rows from error_logs.csv where timestamp is one of {1647736202,1647736380,1647737040} or where timestamp is between 1647736900 and 1647737060 (to capture nearby error messages). Return columns: timestamp, cmdb_id, message (full, untruncated). Also highlight which of those rows correspond to frontend-0/1/2.\nKeep outputs concise and bounded (do not return full time series beyond the requested timestamps). This will let us confirm exact metric values and full error messages at candidate failure minutes for final root-cause determination." }

